OL,5, Some mortgage borrowers who only pay   
OL,6, the interest on their loan are being   
OL,7, "overly optimistic" about their ability
OL,8, to clear their final debt, data shows. 
OL,10,FInterest-only deals require borrowers  
OL,11,Fto have a plan to pay off the loan -   
OL,12,Fknown as the capital - at the end of   
OL,13,Fthe mortgage term.                     
OL,15,FBut research by the Financial Conduct  
OL,16,FAuthority (FCA) suggests some people do
OL,17,Fnot realise they face a shortfall.     
OL,19,FThe warning comes as rising costs mean 
OL,20,Finterest-only deals may become popular.
